                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 329.) I saw the prisoner running across the road, and the prosecutor following him—he passed me at the corner of Salisbury-court with the book—he ran along Salisbury-court, and dropped it—I am sure he is the person—I ran and spoke to the prosecutor, and he pursued the prisoner—he got into the City gas-works, there I lost sight of him, and he was taken by Brissenden.</p>
